  "prompt": "Do employees at Select Income REIT have a good work-life balance? Does this differ across positions and departments?",
  "response": "While I don't have specific, up-to-date information on Select Income REIT's employee experience regarding work-life balance, employee experiences can vary significantly based on a range of factors including position, department, and individual management styles.\n\nIn general, work-life balance can differ across roles within an organization. For example:\n\n1. **Management vs. Non-management Roles:** Managers may have more responsibilities that could lead to longer hours, while non-management roles might have more predictable hours.\n  \n2. **Departments:** Departments like tenant relations or property management may have more rigid hours due to the nature of their work compared to corporate roles in finance or marketing, which might allow for more flexibility.\n\n3. **Company Culture:** The overall culture and policies of Select Income REIT also play a crucial role. Companies that emphasize flexible work schedules, remote work options, and employee well-being generally foster a better work-life balance.\n\n4. **Employee Reviews:** Checking employee reviews on platforms like Glassdoor or Indeed could provide insights into how employees from various positions perceive their work-life balance.\n\nFor the most accurate and specific information, consider looking for employee testimonials or company reviews.",
